Solly Makganato JOHANNESBURG, November 14 – The tax fraud case against television personality Bonang Matheba was postponed again on Wednesday at the Commercial Crimes Court, where her legal team requested a postponement until 27 November. Matheba faces charges for allegedly failing to pay personal tax from 2007 – 2017 and company tax from 2014 – 2017. “We have been engaging with SARS on the matter. We have complied and we are in the process of making representations, and request a further postponement,” Matheba’s lawyer Charl Coetzee told the court The judge granted the postponement, allowing her legal team time to finalise their representations to present to the court. Generations star Seiphemo admits to contravening tax law, case postponed 